<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-12T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.84/908: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-12T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 12,
                                            1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>For the Minister.</p>
                            <p>The Secretary of State has informally suggested to the Japanese
                                delegates in Paris that they make open and specific declaration
                                concerning Shantung. They replied that various considerations among
                                which was Japanese public opinion made this inadvisable. The
                                proposal is still receiving consideration.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>